WEBVTT

00:34.402 --> 00:36.637
HEY.

00:39.039 --> 00:43.511
- KIM. THANK GOD.
- OH, BOB.
[ Sniffing ]

00:43.544 --> 00:46.447
YOU FORGOT TO CHANGE
THE BABY'S DIAPERS.
NO.

00:46.480 --> 00:49.049
THE CAMO DIAPERS.

00:49.083 --> 00:51.119
[ Teddy Crying ]

00:57.425 --> 01:01.295
I DON'T HAVE TIME
TO HOLD YOUR HAND
THROUGH EVERY LITTLE THING.

01:05.633 --> 01:08.236
MOMMY'S GOTTA GO TO WORK.

01:08.269 --> 01:11.439
SHH! QUIET.
THEY'LL HEAR US.

01:11.472 --> 01:13.707
DON RICKLES?
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

01:13.741 --> 01:16.144
I BROUGHT THE RED SASH.

01:17.911 --> 01:20.281
[ Alarm Blaring ]

01:24.952 --> 01:27.121
[ Alarm Clock Beeping ]

01:29.157 --> 01:31.792
[ Serena ]
MOMMY!

01:31.825 --> 01:34.162
[ Beeping Stops ]

01:34.195 --> 01:36.164
MOMMY, WE'RE LATE.

01:39.767 --> 01:42.336
[ Kim ]
HE'S THERE. HE JUST APPEARS.

01:42.370 --> 01:45.806
AND HE HAS A RED RIBBON
OVER HIS SHIRT.

01:45.839 --> 01:50.744
SUBMARINE, CIGAR, TORPEDO?
AND YOUR HUSBAND
WAS ON HIS KNEES?

01:50.778 --> 01:53.147
NOW, THAT'S A DREAM.

01:53.181 --> 01:56.417
- EITHER YOU'RE GETTING
TOO MUCH SEX OR NOT ENOUGH.
- ONLY IN MY DREAMS.

01:56.450 --> 01:59.687
WHERE WAS YOUR HUSBAND
LAST NIGHT AS YOU WERE
DREAMING OF OUR HUSBANDS?

01:59.720 --> 02:01.989
NOT IN MY BED.
ALL NIGHT AT THE OFFICE.

02:02.022 --> 02:04.292
BUT WAIT.
I DIDN'T TELL YOU THE BEST--

02:07.228 --> 02:09.263
BEST PART.

02:09.297 --> 02:11.899
I HAD A SUBMACHINE GUN.

02:17.371 --> 02:20.808
CONTINUE TO AWAIT RADIO CONTACT
WITH SNAKE DOCTOR.

02:20.841 --> 02:22.210
WE GOT AN INTERCEPT.

02:25.313 --> 02:27.147
[ Static On Speaker ]
[ Man Speaking Foreign Language
On Speaker ]

02:27.181 --> 02:29.350
LET ME WASH THAT.
[ Typing ]

02:33.053 --> 02:36.357
THE NORTH KOREA ARMY DETAIL
TALKING TO THE BRIGADE H.Q.

02:36.390 --> 02:38.392
THE SCIENTIST-- THAT'S WHAT
THE N.K. ARMY CALLS HIM--

02:38.426 --> 02:43.331
HAS REQUESTED
CHICKEN NOODLE SOUP AND SOJU.

02:43.364 --> 02:46.400
IT'S A FOUR-HOUR CAR RIDE TO--

02:46.434 --> 02:48.502
- HIS CABIN BY THE SEA.
- THAT'S RIGHT.

02:48.536 --> 02:52.206
OKAY, FOLKS.
PACKAGE IS ON THE MOVE.

02:52.240 --> 02:57.345
OUR DEFECTOR SHOULD ARRIVE
AT RENDEZVOUS HERE
AT 2100 HOURS.

02:57.378 --> 02:59.547
SNAKE DOCTOR
LEFT THE PORT OF MUKO
THREE HOURS AGO.

02:59.580 --> 03:02.416
THEY HAVE 10 HOURS
TO COLLECT OUR SCIENTIST
AND GET HIM OUT.

03:02.450 --> 03:04.852
HAS SNAKE DOCTOR
CONFIRMED HIS POSITION?

03:04.885 --> 03:06.887
ALL RIGHT.
I WANT ALL EYES
ON THE NORTH KOREAN NAVY.

03:06.920 --> 03:11.191
ANY SHIP DEVIATES
OFF ITS PROJECTED PATH,
COME TO TEACHER.

03:11.225 --> 03:13.261
SIR, THE COLONEL NEEDS YOU
IN HIS OFFICE.

03:19.066 --> 03:21.269
THANK YOU.

03:26.407 --> 03:28.442
YOU WANNA READ THIS?

03:30.378 --> 03:35.416
"SOVIET-ERA SUB, ASSASSIN,
WET SUIT, MACK AND JONAS."

03:35.449 --> 03:37.251
NOTE THE HIGHLIGHTED WORDS.

03:40.888 --> 03:42.756
THIS IS A TRANSCRIPT
OF MY WIFE.

03:42.790 --> 03:45.359
- YOU'VE BEEN TALKING IN BED,
SOLDIER?
- SIR, I HAVE NOT.

03:45.393 --> 03:48.562
THEN WHAT IS THIS,
THE WORLD'S WORST COINCIDENCE?

03:48.596 --> 03:51.399
SIR, I WILL SWEAR ON WHATEVER
YOU WANT ME TO SWEAR ON.

03:51.432 --> 03:53.301
HOW IS IT THAT DETAILS
OF A TOP SECRET MISSION...

03:53.334 --> 03:56.470
GOING ON RIGHT NOW
ARE COMING OUT OF
YOUR WIFE'S MOUTH?

03:56.504 --> 03:59.373
SIR, WOULD I BLOW
THREE MONTHS OF MISSION PREP
ON PILLOW TALK?

03:59.407 --> 04:03.544
- THAT'S MY QUESTION, SON.
- COLONEL, IF YOU HAVE THE
SLIGHTEST DOUBT, RELIEVE ME.

04:03.577 --> 04:06.414
WE CROSS THAT LINE,
I AIN'T GONNA NEED
YOUR PERMISSION.

04:06.447 --> 04:08.916
- YOU WANNA CHANGE YOUR STORY?
- NO, SIR.

04:10.451 --> 04:12.920
BACK TO DUTY.

04:12.953 --> 04:15.923
BUT THIS AIN'T OVER.

04:24.264 --> 04:26.467
MOMMY, CAN I HAVE A COOKIE?
[ Tires Screeching ]

04:26.500 --> 04:28.569
SERENA, WAIT TILL WE GET HOME.
DON'T WAKE TEDDY.

04:28.602 --> 04:30.804
HEY, BE CAREFUL!

04:34.041 --> 04:36.744
MS. BROWN,
YOU NEED TO COME WITH US.
I BEG YOUR PARDON?

04:36.777 --> 04:39.279
- RIGHT NOW, PLEASE.
- MOMMY!

04:39.313 --> 04:41.582
SHE'LL BE ALL RIGHT.
IT'S A MATTER
OF NATIONAL SECURITY.

04:41.615 --> 04:44.452
[ Woman ]
HEY, SWEETIE.
YOU CAN COME WITH ME.

04:44.485 --> 04:48.989
COLONEL, WHERE ARE MY KIDS?
WHAT THE HELL'S GOING ON?
THEY-- THEY TOOK MY KIDS.

04:49.022 --> 04:51.425
- THE CHILDREN ARE FINE.
- YOU TOOK THEM?

04:51.459 --> 04:53.661
YES, WE DID.
WHERE ARE THEY?

04:53.694 --> 04:55.963
IN THE CARE OF THE ARMY.
I AM NOT IN
YOUR CHAIN OF COMMAND.

04:55.996 --> 04:59.533
MS. BROWN,
YOUR HUSBAND IS.

04:59.567 --> 05:03.537
A SUSPECTED SECURITY BREACH
TRIGGERS A LEVEL 6 PROTOCOL.

05:03.571 --> 05:07.007
IT INVOLVES YOUR HUSBAND.
YOU WERE OVERHEARD
IN A PUBLIC PLACE.

05:07.040 --> 05:10.043
I WAS TELLING MY FRIENDS
ABOUT A DREAM.

05:10.077 --> 05:13.947
- IS THAT WHAT IT WAS?
- WHAT ARE YOU ACCUSING ME OF?

05:13.981 --> 05:16.316
BECAUSE I DON'T HAVE
TO LISTEN TO IT.
THAT'S RIGHT.

05:16.350 --> 05:19.487
LEGALLY, YOU CAN WALK OFF
WHENEVER THE FANCY STRIKES YOU.
BUT IF YOU DO,

05:19.520 --> 05:21.389
I'LL MAKE SURE YOUR HUSBAND
IS RIGHT IN STEP BEHIND YOU...

05:21.422 --> 05:23.557
OFF THIS BASE
AND OFF THIS JOB FOREVER.

05:28.562 --> 05:31.999
THANK YOU.
DOES BOB EVER
BRING HOME WORK?

05:32.032 --> 05:34.067
OF COURSE NOT.
WE KNOW THE RULES.

05:34.101 --> 05:36.370
BOB SAID HE BROUGHT HOME
SOME PAPERS.
DID YOU EVER LOOK?

05:36.404 --> 05:39.306
CURIOSITY GET THE BETTER
OF YOU, MS. BROWN?

05:39.339 --> 05:43.577
YOU THINK I'M LYING?
GIVE ME A POLY RIGHT NOW.

05:43.611 --> 05:47.047
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA.
AS A MATTER OF FACT,
THEY'RE WAITING FOR US.

05:47.080 --> 05:50.350
POLYGRAPH AND
VOICE ANALYSIS TOO.

05:50.384 --> 05:52.753
LET'S GO.

05:52.786 --> 05:56.323
HAVE YOU SPOKEN TO YOUR HUSBAND
ABOUT HIS MISSIONS?
NO.

05:56.356 --> 05:59.493
[ Man ]
DOES YOUR MOTHER KNOW WHAT
YOUR HUSBAND DOES FOR A LIVING?

05:59.527 --> 06:01.729
[ Kim ]
NO.
SHE'S TELLING THE TRUTH.

06:01.762 --> 06:05.599
[ Man ] HAVE YOU EVER
TOLD ANYONE THE TRUE DESIGNATION
OF YOUR HUSBAND'S UNIT?

06:05.633 --> 06:07.435
[ Kim ]
NO.

06:07.468 --> 06:10.671
DO YOU USE SEX,
OR THE PROMISE OF SEX,
WITH YOUR HUSBAND...

06:10.704 --> 06:12.773
TO DETERMINE WHERE HE IS
ABOUT TO BE DEPLOYED?

06:12.806 --> 06:15.543
YOU KNOW, I REALLY THINK
I'VE HAD ENOUGH.

06:18.579 --> 06:21.415
THANK YOU.
YOU CAN LEAVE.

06:25.252 --> 06:28.456
MS. BROWN, YOU MAY HAVE
PERHAPS CONVINCED THOSE MACHINES
YOU'RE TELLING THE TRUTH--

06:28.489 --> 06:32.593
- BUT?
- THOSE MACHINES DON'T SEND
MEN INTO COMBAT. I DO.

06:34.495 --> 06:37.097
YOU SAY YOUR HUSBAND
DIDN'T TELL YOU?

06:37.130 --> 06:40.067
THEN I NEED YOU TO TELL ME
HOW YOU KNOW WHAT YOU KNOW.

06:40.100 --> 06:43.070
- YOU FEEL LIKE SAVING
YOUR HUSBAND'S JOB?
- I HAD A DREAM.

06:47.641 --> 06:51.579
WHAT'S THE RED RIBBON?
RED RIBBON?

06:51.612 --> 06:54.081
YOU SAID A MAN
ON THE SUBMARINE HAD
A RED RIBBON UNDER HIS JACKET.

06:55.749 --> 06:57.585
A RED RIBBON.

06:57.618 --> 06:59.520
IT WAS JUST A DREAM.

07:09.497 --> 07:11.965
CAPTAIN, IT'S TIME
TO OPEN THE ORDERS.

07:30.818 --> 07:33.253
[ Call And Response ]
* FIRED UP
FIRED UP *

07:33.286 --> 07:35.489
* TWENTY-SEVEN
FIRED UP *

07:35.523 --> 07:37.825
* HERE WE GO
ON THE ROAD *

07:37.858 --> 07:40.127
* TWENTY-SEVEN
FIRED UP *

07:40.160 --> 07:42.663
* FIRED UP
FIRED UP *

07:42.696 --> 07:45.065
* TWENTY-SEVEN
FIRED UP **

07:55.475 --> 07:57.878
PLEASE AUTHENTICATE
THAT THE ORDERS ARE SEALED.

07:57.911 --> 08:00.581
THE SEAL IS NOT BROKEN.

08:12.425 --> 08:14.461
I AM DIRECTED TO--
TURN YOURSELF OVER TO ME.

08:14.494 --> 08:16.864
I COMMAND THIS VESSEL.

08:16.897 --> 08:19.733
I COMMAND THIS MISSION.
TO DO THAT,
I MUST COMMAND THIS SUB.

08:19.767 --> 08:22.903
THOSE ARE YOUR ORDERS
FROM YOUR ADMIRAL.

08:22.936 --> 08:25.038
WE MUST MOVE NOW.

08:30.010 --> 08:32.580
WE'RE RECEIVING FLASH GRAPHIC.

08:41.521 --> 08:44.024
MR. GREEN.

08:44.057 --> 08:45.959
PLOT THESE NEW COORDINATES.

08:47.628 --> 08:50.831
THOSE COORDINATES PUT US
INSIDE NORTH KOREAN WATERS.

08:50.864 --> 08:54.167
THAT'S PROVOCATION.
IF THEY SEE US,
THEY WILL ATTACK,

08:54.201 --> 08:56.670
AND THEY WOULD BE WELL
WITHIN THEIR RIGHTS TO DO SO.

08:56.704 --> 08:59.673
JUST BE SURE THEY CAN'T SEE US.
CHIEF OF THE WATCH,
RIG FOR QUIET.

08:59.707 --> 09:01.875
FLANK SPEED.

09:05.078 --> 09:08.381
THIS BOAT IS OLD.
WE HAVE NO MODERN DEFENSES.

09:08.415 --> 09:12.052
THAT'S WHY WE CHOSE IT.
NOBODY'S LOOKING FOR AN OLD SUB.
WE DO NOT EXIST.

09:12.085 --> 09:14.655
PLEASE ORDER YOUR MEN
TO TAKE THIS BOAT DOWN NOW.

09:28.401 --> 09:30.470
[ Klaxon Blaring ]

09:42.783 --> 09:44.818
IT'S UNDERSTANDABLE.
IT'S YOUR FIRST
MISSION OVERSIGHT.

09:44.852 --> 09:46.887
YOU WANNA CROW ABOUT IT
TO YOUR OLD LADY,
EXPLAIN TO HER...

09:46.920 --> 09:48.789
WHY YOU'RE NOT AT HOME
WASHING THE DISHES.

09:48.822 --> 09:52.125
IT'S NOT LIKE THAT.
IF YOU TELL ME THAT'S
THE WAY IT'S GOING DOWN,

09:52.159 --> 09:55.128
THAT IT'S CONTAINABLE
TO JUST YOUR WIFE, THEN I CAN
PROCEED WITH THE MISSION.

09:55.162 --> 09:57.765
IF YOU TELL ME IT DIDN'T,
THEN I'VE GOT
AN UNEXPLAINED LEAK...

09:57.798 --> 10:00.567
THAT BY NOW
COULD'VE WORKED ITS WAY
ALL THE WAY TO NORTH KOREA.

10:00.600 --> 10:03.170
I NEED TO KNOW.
MY MEN HIT THE SHORE, ARE THEY
GONNA GET THEIR ASSES SHOT OFF?

10:03.203 --> 10:05.739
I DIDN'T SAY A WORD TO HER.
THEN WE HAVE A PROBLEM,
DON'T WE?

10:05.773 --> 10:08.241
SIR, WE HAVE A LIMITED WINDOW
TO GET THIS DEFECTOR OUT.

10:08.275 --> 10:13.146
THE ENTIRE NORTH KOREAN NAVY
IS HERE AND HERE MONITORING
OUR JOINT FLEET EXERCISE,

10:13.180 --> 10:16.249
AND I'M THE ONLY ONE
IN THE ROOM WHO HAS STUDIED
THEIR NAVY'S MANEUVERS.

10:16.283 --> 10:19.687
NO ONE IS LOOKING
FOR AN OLD SUB, BUT THEY ARE
LOOKING FOR OUR OTHER BOATS.

10:19.720 --> 10:22.923
THE NAVY IS GONNA DRAW
THEM AWAY, BUT THAT SUB WILL
STILL HAVE TO THREAD THE NEEDLE,

10:22.956 --> 10:24.825
AND I'M THE BEST PERSON
TO ASSIST THEM.

10:24.858 --> 10:26.827
OUR PACKAGE IS EN ROUTE
TO HIS HOUSE BY THE SEA NOW.

10:26.860 --> 10:30.197
LET ME BRING THE TEAM HOME,
COLONEL.
I'M GONNA MONITOR YOUR COMM.

10:30.230 --> 10:33.133
NO OUTSIDE CALLS,
EYES ALWAYS ON YOU.

10:33.166 --> 10:36.369
WHEN IT COMES TIME TO BLOW
THE WHISTLE TO SEND THE MEN
ON SHORE, I'LL GIVE THE WORD.

10:36.403 --> 10:39.372
MAY I ALSO ASK--
THAT'LL BE ALL.

10:42.575 --> 10:46.613
I CAN'T THINK OF
ONE RATIONAL REASON
WHY SHE KNOWS WHAT SHE KNOWS...

10:46.646 --> 10:49.683
OTHER THAN HER HUSBAND
SPOKE OUT OF SCHOOL
AND JUST GAVE UP A CAREER.

10:49.717 --> 10:51.685
I DON'T WANT THAT.

10:51.719 --> 10:54.688
SO I'M TO EXPLORE
THE IRRATIONAL SIDE OF THIS?

10:54.722 --> 10:57.390
THE INFORMATION I REQUIRE:
ARE WE DEALING WITH
A SECURITY BREACH?

10:57.424 --> 10:59.659
AND WHAT IF WE'RE NOT?

10:59.693 --> 11:03.563
WELL, THIS DREAM BUSINESS
IS YOUR WORLD, NOT MINE.
I'M JUST VISITING.

11:03.596 --> 11:07.334
I JUST NEED TO KNOW
IN GOOD OLD-FASHIONED TERMS
WHAT THE HELL'S GOING ON.

11:07.367 --> 11:10.503
HERE'S KIM BROWN'S FILE.

11:10.537 --> 11:14.742
SHE KNOWS I'M COMING.
SHE DAMN SURE KNOWS
SOMEBODY'S COMING.

11:16.777 --> 11:18.912
YOU GONNA GIVE ME
ANOTHER POLYGRAPH?
[ Woman ] NO.

11:18.946 --> 11:23.250
- I CAN READ YOUR MIND.
- ALL RIGHT.

11:23.283 --> 11:25.052
YOU'RE WORRIED
ABOUT YOUR CHILDREN.

11:25.085 --> 11:26.920
WELL, THAT'S RIGHT.
TEDDY AND SERENA.

11:26.954 --> 11:29.022
YOU READ MY FILE.

11:29.056 --> 11:31.691
NO.
AND YOUR CHILDREN ARE FINE.

11:31.725 --> 11:34.728
THEY'RE WITH YOUR FRIENDS NOW--
TIFFANY AND MOLLY.

11:34.762 --> 11:38.698
WAIT A MINUTE.
I KNOW WHO YOU ARE.

11:38.732 --> 11:42.002
DO YOU?
I SAW A THING ON YOU
IN THE ARMY TIMES.

11:42.035 --> 11:44.537
YES?
YOU'RE THE GOAT LADY.

11:44.571 --> 11:47.741
YOU'RE THE PSYCHIATRIST
WHO DID THAT EXPERIMENT...

11:47.775 --> 11:50.944
WHERE YOU TRIED
TO BURST A GOAT'S HEART
JUST BY STARING AT IT.

11:50.978 --> 11:54.848
THAT'S AN AMUSING
BUT NOT ACCURATE DESCRIPTION.

11:54.882 --> 11:57.785
THAT'S WHAT YOU DO.
DOES THAT SEEM
IMPOSSIBLE TO YOU?

11:57.818 --> 12:01.855
AT A TRAFFIC LIGHT,
CAN YOU FEEL IF SOMEONE
IS WATCHING YOU?

12:01.889 --> 12:04.124
YES.
HOW?

12:04.157 --> 12:07.961
I'M IN MILITARY INTELLIGENCE,
RESEARCH.

12:07.995 --> 12:11.231
DREAMS, TELEKINESIS
AND PSYCHIC PHENOMENA.

12:11.264 --> 12:14.367
BUT WHY ARE YOU HERE?
YOU HAD A DREAM.

12:14.401 --> 12:15.969
AND SO I WOULD LIKE
TO TALK TO YOU.

12:16.003 --> 12:18.806
HERE'S WHAT WE CAN DO.

12:18.839 --> 12:22.810
WE CAN GO BACK
INSIDE THAT DREAM...

12:22.843 --> 12:24.744
AND SEE IF
WE CAN HELP YOUR HUSBAND.

12:24.778 --> 12:26.746
THAT'S WHAT WE CAN DO.

12:28.581 --> 12:32.719
- TO HELP MY HUSBAND?
- ARE YOU INCLINED
TO TAKE THAT RISK?

12:32.752 --> 12:35.455
ARE YOU?

12:35.488 --> 12:37.157
IF YOU WANT TO PROCEED,
BLINK TWICE.

12:41.795 --> 12:43.831
I'M GOING TO PUT YOU
IN A TRANCE.

12:43.864 --> 12:46.733
A TRANCE?
IT WILL FEEL
QUITE FAMILIAR.

12:46.766 --> 12:49.269
YOU'LL BE LUCID,
ABLE TO THINK,
ABLE TO TALK.

12:49.302 --> 12:51.839
YOU'RE LOOKING
AT MY EYES. GOOD.

12:51.872 --> 12:54.674
THAT'S GOOD.

12:54.707 --> 12:57.945
WOULD YOU COUNT THE NUMBER
OF TIMES I BLINK?

13:01.882 --> 13:05.552
WOULD YOU COUNT THEM?
ONE.

13:07.855 --> 13:10.490
TWO.

13:10.523 --> 13:14.261
THREE.
TAKE ME BACK
TO THE SUBMARINE.

13:14.294 --> 13:17.297
HOW DID YOU GET THERE?
I--

13:17.330 --> 13:20.000
THAT'S RIGHT.
THE INTERESTING PART.

13:20.033 --> 13:24.304
THE PART YOU HAVEN'T
TOLD ANYONE ELSE.

13:26.039 --> 13:28.341
[ Kim ]
I WAS IN THIS NARROW SPACE.

13:31.011 --> 13:32.846
LIKE A TUBE.

13:36.249 --> 13:38.251
I LIKED IT.

13:39.519 --> 13:42.489
AND...

13:42.522 --> 13:46.259
THEN I WAS IN
THE SUBMARINE.

13:58.906 --> 14:01.274
I WAS SEARCHING FOR SOMETHING.

14:24.131 --> 14:27.034
** [ Ragtime, Faint ]

14:27.067 --> 14:29.937
I COULD HEAR MUSIC,
LIKE A BAND,

14:32.072 --> 14:34.074
COMING FROM THE ENGINE ROOM.

14:42.282 --> 14:44.751
** [ Continues ]

15:08.141 --> 15:12.045
HELLO, MY CHILD.
I'M IN THE WRONG PLACE.

15:12.079 --> 15:14.214
NO.
WE'VE BEEN EXPECTING YOU.

15:14.247 --> 15:16.083
YOU HAVE?
YES. WELCOME.

15:16.116 --> 15:18.986
WELCOME.
WHAT CHURCH IS THIS?

15:19.019 --> 15:21.588
THIS IS WHERE
THE SUB-MARINERS--
ISN'T IT SUBMARINERS?

15:21.621 --> 15:26.159
TOMATOES, POTATOES.
YOU ASK AN OLD JEW.
THEY ALL COME HERE TO DIE.

15:31.098 --> 15:35.268
I DON'T WANT TO BE HERE.
YOU THINK THEY WANNA
BE HERE?

15:46.046 --> 15:49.316
JONAS?
JONAS, WAKE UP.

15:58.291 --> 16:00.293
MACK?

16:08.135 --> 16:11.371
I'M SO SORRY FOR YOUR LOSS.
YOU KILLED THEM.

16:11.404 --> 16:13.840
WHAT KIND OF FRIEND ARE YOU?

16:13.873 --> 16:17.044
** [ Ragtime ]

16:30.157 --> 16:32.525
GIVE MY REGARDS
TO YOUR DAUGHTER.

16:40.100 --> 16:42.335
PULL UP THEIR MAPS.
I WANNA SEE
THEIR RED HERRINGS LIVE.

16:47.207 --> 16:49.242
ARE ALL THEIR
ATTACK SUBS ACCOUNTED FOR?

16:49.276 --> 16:52.879
HERE AND HERE,
AND 11 DIESELS TASKED HERE
ALL PLAYING PUSS IN THE CORNER.

16:52.912 --> 16:54.881
GOOD. KEEP MONITORING
THEIR SCREWS.

16:54.914 --> 16:57.384
I WANNA KNOW
EVERY TURN THEY MAKE.

16:57.417 --> 17:00.153
AND THESE BATTLESHIPS HERE
IN THE YELLOW SEA?

17:00.187 --> 17:03.256
PROCEEDING TO JOIN THE THREE
SOUTH KOREAN SUBS HERE.

17:03.290 --> 17:05.692
MM-HMM.
THAT OPENS OUR PATH HERE.

17:08.295 --> 17:10.263
YEAH. THAT'S OUR MOST
DIRECT INGRESS.

17:10.297 --> 17:13.032
COMMUNICATE THOSE COORDINATES
TO SNAKE DOCTOR
WHEN HE COMES UP.

17:13.066 --> 17:15.202
LET'S TAKE A CLOSER LOOK.

17:18.071 --> 17:19.672
WHAT'S HAPPENING THERE?

17:19.706 --> 17:21.841
FLEET MONITOR, ARE YOU AWARE
THAT YOUR RED HERRING...

17:21.874 --> 17:24.244
DIDN'T PULL
NORTH KOREAN DESTROYER...

17:24.277 --> 17:28.215
0541 HERCULES CLASS
OFF ITS PATROL GRID?

17:28.248 --> 17:34.053
- POSIT SIGNET, LINE TWO.
- I AUTHENTICATE--
LIMA-DELTA-SIERRA.

17:34.087 --> 17:35.955
[ Man On Speaker ]
THIS IS GOLDFINGER
2-3-GOLF-YANKEE-VICTOR.

17:35.988 --> 17:39.126
ROGER, GOLDFINGER 2-3.
PLEASE ADVISE.

17:39.159 --> 17:43.563
IS THAT AN N.K. WARSHIP
BEARING SOUTH 1-NINER-3
ON AN INTERSECTING VECTOR?

17:43.596 --> 17:46.233
TELL ME THAT'S NOT
A DESTROYER GALLOPING OUR WAY.

17:48.401 --> 17:50.137
- YES, SIR.
- HOW SERIOUS?

17:50.170 --> 17:53.106
I DON'T KNOW.

17:56.075 --> 17:59.312
WE GOT A DESTROYER
THAT DIDN'T TAKE THE BAIT.
FIND ME ITS PATROL GRID.

17:59.346 --> 18:03.483
THE ONLY THING I WANT TO KNOW
IS WILL THAT DESTROYER
CROSS PATHS WITH OUR SUB?

18:08.855 --> 18:11.391
WE JUST CROSSED INTO
NORTH KOREAN WATERS.

18:11.424 --> 18:14.127
HOLD THIS DEPTH,
ULTRA QUIET.

18:16.163 --> 18:18.831
IN 20 MINUTES, WE SHOULD
BE AT CHECKPOINT BRAVO.

18:18.865 --> 18:22.302
ALL CLEAR SO FAR.

18:22.335 --> 18:26.173
[ Water Dripping ]

18:26.206 --> 18:28.775
THAT'S WHY
I DIDN'T BECOME A SEAL.
IT JUST AIN'T NATURAL.

18:28.808 --> 18:31.077
WHAT? YOU'RE AFRAID
OF A LITTLE MOISTURE?

18:31.110 --> 18:34.247
YEAH, WHEN IT'S UP TO
370 POUNDS PER SQUARE INCH.

18:34.281 --> 18:39.286
WE'RE A FOOTBALL FIELD DEEP.
ASK THE X.O. HOW FAR DOWN
THIS OLD HEAP OF PIG IRON GOES.

18:43.523 --> 18:45.658
900 FEET.

18:45.692 --> 18:47.294
AND THEN WHAT?
BOOM!

18:50.330 --> 18:52.299
YOUR FIRST TIME ON SUB?

18:52.332 --> 18:55.134
VIRGIN.

18:55.168 --> 18:58.438
[ Pipe Bursts ]

18:58.471 --> 19:00.240
[ Excited Chattering ]

19:04.911 --> 19:06.779
LOVING IT SO FAR.

19:06.813 --> 19:09.849
WE'RE HERE TO HELP YOU.
THANK YOU.

19:09.882 --> 19:15.021
I ONLY WISH I KNEW WHAT YOUR
ULTIMATE GOAL IS SO I COULD
BE OF GREATER ASSISTANCE.

19:15.054 --> 19:17.290
A SMALL REQUEST.
YOUR SIDEARM, SIR.

19:17.324 --> 19:21.261
WOULD YOU STORE THEM
IN OUR ARMS LOCKER?
IT MAKES MY CREW NERVOUS.

19:23.663 --> 19:27.234
DESIGNATED SIERRA ONE.
8,000 YARDS, CLOSING RAPIDLY.

19:29.202 --> 19:31.704
ENEMY DESTROYER CLOSING IN.
WE NEED TO HUSTLE.

19:31.738 --> 19:33.506
FLANK SPEED.
NO.

19:33.540 --> 19:36.876
CAVITATION WILL BE TOO LOUD.
GO DEAD IN THE WATER.

19:36.909 --> 19:40.313
HE'S NOT LOOKING FOR US.
WE DON'T EXIST.

19:40.347 --> 19:43.250
IF YOU'RE WRONG,
HE DEPTH-CHARGES US,
WE ALL DROWN.

19:43.283 --> 19:45.918
- HE'S BEARING 1-9-4 DEGREES
AND CLOSING RAPIDLY.
- WHAT'S OUR DEPTH?

19:45.952 --> 19:47.987
400 FEET.

19:48.020 --> 19:50.423
BECOME A DEAD CONTACT
IN THE WATER.

19:50.457 --> 19:54.060
ALL ENGINES STOP.
DON'T TURN A SCREW.
JUST FLOAT.

20:05.405 --> 20:08.441
HE'S IN THE PATROL BOX.
HE'LL TURN.

20:08.475 --> 20:11.878
IF WE DRIFT OUTSIDE
HIS PATROL BOX, HE'LL STOP.

20:11.911 --> 20:14.547
HE WON'T FOLLOW.
HE DOESN'T EVEN KNOW
WE'RE HERE.

20:14.581 --> 20:17.049
I DON'T KNOW THE QUADRANTS
OF HIS PATROL BOX.

20:17.083 --> 20:20.453
WE DO.
42/58.

20:20.487 --> 20:24.223
HE'S IN A CRISSCROSS PATTERN.
HE'LL TURN 40 DEGREES WEST.

20:24.257 --> 20:27.093
400 YARDS.
AND CLOSING.

20:30.763 --> 20:34.434
SHE'S TURNING.
ENEMY DESTROYER'S
TURNING DUE WEST.

20:40.006 --> 20:42.108
WHY IS SHE DREAMING
ABOUT DON RICKLES?

20:42.141 --> 20:44.110
HE'S HER FATHER'S
FAVORITE COMEDIAN.

20:44.143 --> 20:46.413
IS IT ALWAYS ABOUT DADDY
WITH YOU HEAD DOCTORS?

20:46.446 --> 20:49.416
WHY DO YOU THINK
YOUR BOYS JOIN THE ARMY?

20:49.449 --> 20:51.451
WHY DO YOU THINK GIRLS
MARRY SOLDIERS?

20:51.484 --> 20:55.422
YOU'RE EITHER
RUNNING TOWARDS DADDY
OR RUNNING AWAY FROM HIM.

20:55.455 --> 20:57.590
IN HER DREAM, IT'S A FUNERAL.

20:57.624 --> 21:00.593
A SPECIAL SERVICE
FOR SUBMARINERS.

21:00.627 --> 21:03.496
- AND IN THE CASKETS?
- THREE OF YOUR MEN.

21:03.530 --> 21:07.099
AND THEY DON'T WINK,
JOKE, SMILE? I MEAN,
THERE'S A FAMOUS COMEDIAN THERE.

21:07.133 --> 21:10.102
NO. IT'S A FUNERAL.
TO HER, THEY WERE ALL DEAD.

21:11.804 --> 21:14.441
HE GAVE HER SOMETHING,
UH, FOR LUCK.

21:14.474 --> 21:15.942
DON RICKLES?
WHAT?

21:15.975 --> 21:18.445
A RED CLOVER.

21:20.279 --> 21:22.248
DOES THAT MEAN
SOMETHING TO YOU?

21:22.281 --> 21:24.817
EXCUSE ME.

21:33.059 --> 21:34.794
HAND ME YOUR HEADSET.

21:37.129 --> 21:40.166
NOW I NEED YOU
TO QUIETLY WALK UP THOSE STAIRS
AND SIT THIS ONE OUT.

21:40.199 --> 21:42.602
COLONEL, I PLANNED THIS.
I KNOW EVERY DETAIL.

21:42.635 --> 21:45.304
NOBODY ELSE IN THIS ROOM
IS AS CAPABLE AS I AM--

21:45.338 --> 21:48.341
WE HAVE A SITUATION THAT
REQUIRES YOU TO SIT
THIS ONE OUT. UPSTAIRS, NOW.

21:51.411 --> 21:54.347
GET ME
PACIFIC FLEET COMMAND.
YES, SIR.

21:56.849 --> 21:59.952
THIS IS OUR INSERTION POINT
200 YARDS OFFSHORE.

21:59.986 --> 22:03.490
HERE'S THE BEACH.
WHAT IF WE'RE STILL SIX HOURS
LATE AND THE TIDE'S OUT?

22:03.523 --> 22:04.891
IMPROVISE.
NO.

22:04.924 --> 22:07.059
WE ABORT.
MUD.

22:07.093 --> 22:11.297
IN '89, WHEN SEAL TEAM SIX
WENT INTO PANAMA,
ALL GOT KILLED.

22:11.330 --> 22:13.332
HALF A MILE OF MUD
KILLED THE TEAM.

22:13.366 --> 22:16.369
- WHAT'S THE GRADIENT
OF THE BEACH?
- FIFTEEN DEGREES.

22:16.403 --> 22:19.338
WILL THAT GIVE US ENOUGH COVER,
OR DOES THAT PUT US IN
A KILL ZONE LIKE NORMANDY?

22:19.372 --> 22:22.575
DAYLIGHT BY THE TIME
WE GET TO THE WOODS.

22:22.609 --> 22:25.378
HERE.
MAIN ROADS HERE TO HERE.

22:25.412 --> 22:29.516
WE ACQUIRE
THE PACKAGE HERE.
HIS COTTAGE.

22:29.549 --> 22:31.884
HE'LL BE THERE WAITING,
READY TO GO.

22:31.918 --> 22:33.986
[ Speaking Foreign Language ]
WHAT?

22:34.020 --> 22:36.556
EXACTLY.
I'LL DO THE TALKING.

22:36.589 --> 22:38.425
AND WHAT IF THERE'S
A NEED FOR WEAPONS?

23:00.312 --> 23:02.549
WE HAVEN'T HAD CONTACT.

23:02.582 --> 23:05.384
THEY HAVE TO COME UP
TO PERISCOPE DEPTH
TO SEND AND RECEIVE.

23:05.418 --> 23:08.421
HOW LONG THEY BEEN UNDER?
ELEVEN HOURS NOW, SIR.

23:17.730 --> 23:21.400
MR. BLUE.
CHECK YOUR G.P.S.

23:25.605 --> 23:27.640
THIRTEEN MILES
OFF COURSE.

23:31.511 --> 23:35.047
YOU CHANGED OUR COURSE.
THERE IS LESS RISK
IF WE GO THIS WAY.

23:35.081 --> 23:37.884
WE DON'T HAVE TIME FOR THIS.
IT WILL GET US TO OUR
INSERTION POINT TOO LATE.

23:37.917 --> 23:42.655
WITH RESPECT,
WE ARE HEADING TOWARD THE DAY
OF KOREAN REUNIFICATION.

23:42.689 --> 23:47.560
FOR US TO ENGAGE IN ANY
SORT OF BATTLE COULD SPARK
A WAR AND RUIN THAT HOPE.

23:47.594 --> 23:51.130
I CHOSE THE SAFEST PATH
TO YOUR DESTINATION.

23:51.163 --> 23:54.233
WE'VE GOT TO GET TO
OUR RENDEZVOUS BY HIGH TIDE.

23:54.266 --> 23:57.470
IF YOU HAVE A PROBLEM
TAKING ORDERS FROM ME,
THEN STEP AWAY FROM THE CONN.

24:00.372 --> 24:03.242
- I DO NOT UNDERSTAND. WHY--
- THERE'S NOTHING TO UNDERSTAND.

24:03.275 --> 24:05.978
STAND DOWN, PLEASE.

24:08.014 --> 24:11.784
OF COURSE.
MY APOLOGIES.

24:13.686 --> 24:16.623
GET US BACK
ON OUR ORIGINAL COURSE.
WE NEED TO MAKE UP TIME.

24:20.560 --> 24:22.161
[ Men Speaking Korean ]

24:35.374 --> 24:38.545
THIRTY-TWO MINUTES
TO RENDEZVOUS POINT.
GET OUR ORDERS.

24:38.578 --> 24:41.047
- FROM YOUR COUNTRY?
- YES, FROM MY COUNTRY.

24:41.080 --> 24:44.851
THE FASTER WE GO,
THE LOUDER WE ARE IN THE WATER.

24:44.884 --> 24:47.554
- [ Sonar Pings Loudly ]
- [ Chattering In Korean ]

24:47.587 --> 24:49.488
SONAR JUST SENT OUT A PING.

24:49.522 --> 24:51.658
- HOW THE HELL--
- [ Weapon Cocks ]

24:51.691 --> 24:54.126
TAKE OUT YOUR WEAPONS SLOWLY.

24:54.160 --> 24:56.162
THEY'VE HEARD US.
WE HAVE NO CHOICE
BUT TO TURN AROUND NOW.

24:56.195 --> 24:58.330
WE ARE NOT TURNING AROUND.

24:58.364 --> 25:00.667
X.O., TAKE THEIR WEAPONS.

25:07.574 --> 25:11.878
KILL ME.
BUT IF THEY HEARD THAT PING,
THEY'LL KILL US ALL.

25:11.911 --> 25:14.046
THEN I'LL BE A MARTYR.

25:14.080 --> 25:15.982
FOR THE NORTH KOREANS?

25:16.015 --> 25:18.050
FOR A UNITED KOREA.
[ Ping ]

25:19.752 --> 25:24.056
WE'VE GOT AN ENEMY
SUB-HUNTING PLANE ABOVE US
LOOKING FOR US.

25:24.090 --> 25:26.559
NORTH KOREANS HEARD THE PING.

25:26.593 --> 25:30.663
CAPTAIN, YOU'VE GOT
A DECISION TO MAKE.
THINK OF YOUR FAMILY.

25:30.697 --> 25:33.933
I AM THINKING
OF MY FAMILY.
[ Gunshot ]

25:38.571 --> 25:40.339
- WE GOT CONTACT!
- LET'S GET AN I.D.

25:40.372 --> 25:43.175
I'M ON IT.

25:43.209 --> 25:47.246
WE HAVE A NORTH KOREAN DESTROYER
BEARING 1-NINER-6
AT 6,000 YARDS AND CLOSING.

25:47.279 --> 25:49.616
THEY'RE COMING
RIGHT AT US, TOP.

25:59.926 --> 26:02.128
ALL RIGHT.
PREPARE TO DIVE.

26:14.140 --> 26:19.712
IN YOUR DREAM,
THE PRIEST, YOU SAID,
GAVE YOU A RED CLOVER.

26:19.746 --> 26:23.750
I CAN'T HELP YOU.
I DON'T HAVE
ANY SPECIAL POWERS.

26:23.783 --> 26:25.952
I'M NOT SAYING
THAT YOU DO.
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

26:25.985 --> 26:29.321
I HAD A DREAM.
I AM NOT A FREAK.

26:29.355 --> 26:33.425
I DON'T BELIEVE
IN THE WORLD YOU SAY EXISTS.
THIS IS MY LIFE.

26:33.459 --> 26:38.230
DIRTY DISHES, DIRTY DIAPERS.
THIS IS ALL THE LIFE THERE IS.

26:38.264 --> 26:40.599
WHAT COMES UP
WHEN YOU HEAR THE TERM
"RED CLOVER"?

26:40.633 --> 26:42.501
WHY IS THAT SO IMPORTANT?

26:42.534 --> 26:45.604
I CAN'T TELL YOU.
CAN YOU TELL ME?

26:45.638 --> 26:48.841
WHAT THE HELL IS IT
YOU DO STARING AT GOATS?

26:48.875 --> 26:51.510
DOES THAT SOUND
NORMAL TO YOU,

26:51.543 --> 26:54.280
TRYING TO KILL ANIMALS
BY STARING AT THEM?

26:54.313 --> 26:56.649
- WE WONDERED--
- YES?

26:56.683 --> 27:00.186
IF WE COULD
HARNESS THE MIND--
AS A WEAPON.

27:00.219 --> 27:02.521
AND HOW DOES THAT WORK?
TELL ME HOW THAT WORKS.

27:02.554 --> 27:04.691
HAVE YOU EVER
AT THE SAME TIME...

27:04.724 --> 27:07.326
UTTERED THE SAME THOUGHT
AS YOUR HUSBAND?

27:07.359 --> 27:08.961
OF COURSE YOU HAVE.

27:08.995 --> 27:11.998
EVERYONE HAS.

27:12.031 --> 27:15.968
YOU SPOKE OF THINGS KNOWN
TO YOUR HUSBAND.

27:16.002 --> 27:18.137
EITHER HE TOLD YOU
THOSE THINGS,

27:18.170 --> 27:21.640
WHICH IS A CRIMINAL OFFENSE,
OR YOU SOMEHOW--

27:21.674 --> 27:25.945
I COULD NOT HAVE INTUITED
A TOP SECRET MISSION.
I DON'T HAVE ANY SPECIAL POWERS.

27:25.978 --> 27:30.049
WELL, THEN HOW DO YOU KNOW
THE PHRASE "RED CLOVER"?

27:30.082 --> 27:32.318
IT WAS A COINCIDENCE.
I SAW IT SOMEWHERE.

27:32.351 --> 27:35.722
- WHAT DID YOU DO YESTERDAY?
- I--

27:35.755 --> 27:37.890
DID YOU ROB A BANK?
NO.

27:37.924 --> 27:42.361
DID YOU, UH,
PERFORM AN OPERATION,
OR ABDUCT A CHILD FROM SCHOOL?

27:42.394 --> 27:45.531
- NO.
- DID YOU SLEEP WITH
ANOTHER MAN OR WOMAN?

27:45.564 --> 27:50.402
DID YOU DO ANYTHING
TO BREAK THE LAW IN ANY WAY?

27:50.436 --> 27:52.872
NO.

27:52.905 --> 27:55.708
YOU HAVE NOTHING TO HIDE THEN.

27:55.742 --> 27:58.177
NOW, WHAT DID YOU DO YESTERDAY?

28:00.780 --> 28:03.549
WE'LL GO BACK
TO THE NIGHT BEFORE.
SHOW ME YOUR BEDROOM.

28:08.955 --> 28:12.859
YOU WERE ALONE
LAST NIGHT IN HERE
AFTER BOB LEFT FOR WORK.

28:12.892 --> 28:17.396
IN BED?
YES.

28:17.429 --> 28:19.866
GET INTO BED.

28:19.899 --> 28:22.134
YES, NOW.

28:25.071 --> 28:27.874
HOW DID YOU FALL ASLEEP?

28:27.907 --> 28:30.777
WITH THE TV ON
JUST TO KEEP ME COMPANY.
I LIKE OLD MOVIES.

28:30.810 --> 28:32.845
WHAT WERE YOU WATCHING?

28:32.879 --> 28:35.347
IT WAS A BLACK-AND-WHITE FILM
WITH GREGORY PECK...

28:35.381 --> 28:37.917
AND, I THINK, AVA GARDNER,
ABOUT THE END OF THE WORLD.

28:37.950 --> 28:40.552
THERE IS A SUBMARINE
IN IT.

28:40.586 --> 28:43.522
- I DIDN'T WATCH THAT PART.
- WHY NOT?

28:43.555 --> 28:45.758
THAT PART DISTURBS ME.

28:45.792 --> 28:48.560
THAT'S RIGHT.

28:48.594 --> 28:51.931
YOU WERE WATCHING IT,
THOUGH YOU WERE ASLEEP.

28:51.964 --> 28:55.301
ERGO, YOU DREAMED
A SUBMARINE.

28:55.334 --> 28:58.905
AND RED CLOVER.

28:58.938 --> 29:00.807
MAYBE IT WAS
FROM THE MOVIE TOO?

29:00.840 --> 29:05.311
WE WATCHED THE MOVIE.
THERE WAS NO MENTION
OF RED CLOVER.

29:05.344 --> 29:07.880
I WENT THROUGH BROWN'S
MEDICAL RECORDS.

29:07.914 --> 29:11.117
HE DOESN'T TALK IN HIS SLEEP.
LIKE ALL YOUR MEN,
HE'S WELL-TRAINED.

29:13.085 --> 29:14.954
[ Woman On Speaker ]
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT DAFFODILS ARE?

29:14.987 --> 29:16.789
[ Serena On Speaker ]
YES.

29:16.823 --> 29:19.992
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT DAISIES ARE?
OF COURSE.

29:20.026 --> 29:21.928
HAVE YOU EVER HEARD
OF RED CLOVER?
SURE.

29:21.961 --> 29:24.730
FROM WHO?
MY DADDY.

29:24.763 --> 29:28.700
YOU HEARD YOUR DADDY SAY--
MY DADDY SAYS "RED CLOVER"
A BUNCH OF TIMES.

29:34.874 --> 29:37.276
YOUR DAUGHTER
JUST SOLD YOU OUT.

29:37.309 --> 29:40.612
YOUR WIFE AND DAUGHTER
KNOW DETAILS OF A MISSION...

29:40.646 --> 29:42.849
INCLUDING AN INSERTION POINT
BEHIND ENEMY LINES...

29:42.882 --> 29:45.852
AND THE CODE OF WHICH
EVEN THE SECRETARY OF DEFENSE
DOESN'T KNOW.

29:45.885 --> 29:48.020
I'M SHUTTIN' YOU DOWN.

29:50.689 --> 29:53.993
PREPARE TO SEND
"MISSION ABORT."

29:54.026 --> 29:55.794
WE HAVE NO RADIO CONTACT.
THEY WON'T GET THE ORDER.

30:02.801 --> 30:05.872
- [ Pings ]
- SIR, WE HAVE
AN UNIDENTIFIED SPLASH.

30:05.905 --> 30:08.007
THAT'S A SONAR BUOY
DROPPED BY AN AIRPLANE.

30:08.040 --> 30:11.043
- DESTROYER BEARING FROM 0-4-7.
- I THOUGHT THEY DIDN'T KNOW
WE'RE HERE.

30:11.077 --> 30:13.880
THEY DON'T.
BUT IF WE DON'T MOVE, THEY WILL.

30:13.913 --> 30:16.815
- THEY'RE TRYING TO TRIANGULATE
OUR LOCATION.
- TAKE HER DEEP.

30:36.735 --> 30:39.571
- HOW DEEP, TOP?
- BELOW THE THERMAL.
700 FEET.

30:42.875 --> 30:44.843
[ Pipe Hissing ]

30:58.457 --> 31:02.428
[ Hull Creaking ]

31:02.461 --> 31:05.797
- IF THE BUOY GOES ACTIVE--
- WE'LL HEAR THEIR PINGS.

31:11.803 --> 31:14.240
- [ Sonar Pinging ]
- BUOY HAS GONE ACTIVE.

31:14.273 --> 31:16.708
WE GOTTA GO DEEPER.

31:16.742 --> 31:20.279
- HOW DEEP?
- PUT IT ON THE BOTTOM.

31:20.312 --> 31:21.914
WE GOTTA GET LOST
IN THE SCATTER.

31:27.119 --> 31:29.121
[ Glass Breaking ]

31:32.291 --> 31:34.660
CHIEF OF WATCH,
FLOOD THE BALLAST TANK.

31:45.804 --> 31:47.974
THE BOTTOM IS
900 FEET, TOP.

31:50.109 --> 31:52.711
- SIR, THAT'S--
- I KNOW WHAT IT IS.

31:52.744 --> 31:54.746
AT 700 FEET,
THIS SUB COULD CRACK.

31:56.315 --> 31:58.184
YEAH. I KNOW.

32:02.121 --> 32:04.123
[ Door Opens ]

32:05.857 --> 32:07.994
I WANNA SEE MY HUSBAND.

32:08.027 --> 32:10.496
HOW IS IT THAT BOTH
YOU AND YOUR DAUGHTER
KNOW THE TERM "RED CLOVER"?

32:12.498 --> 32:14.967
HELP ME FIND OUT.
GOOD.

32:21.974 --> 32:24.510
[ Psychiatrist ]
TELL ME WHAT YOU SEE.

32:28.947 --> 32:32.151
I'M IN SERENA'S ROOM.

32:32.184 --> 32:35.587
AND BOB'S READING TO HER.

32:35.621 --> 32:38.757
"FIRST, THE WHITE RABBIT
WENT INTO THE GARDEN.

32:38.790 --> 32:42.094
"AFTER WHITE RABBIT HAD STOLEN
THE CARROT FROM THE GARDEN,

32:42.128 --> 32:43.996
HE HID IN
THE DEEP RED CLOVER."

32:44.030 --> 32:48.100
[ Psychiatrist ]
GOOD, KIM. NOW LOOK AT
THE SPINE OF THE BOOK.

32:48.134 --> 32:51.037
WHAT DOES IT SAY?

32:51.070 --> 32:53.039
[ Kim ]
IT'S FROM THE SCHOOL LIBRARY.

32:53.072 --> 32:55.741
"THE ADVENTURES
OF WHITE RABBIT."

33:09.521 --> 33:12.324
AN AMBULANCE.

33:12.358 --> 33:15.861
THERE WAS AN AMBULANCE
IN THE TREE.

33:15.894 --> 33:17.996
[ Psychiatrist ]
FINISH YOUR DRAWING.

33:21.267 --> 33:22.934
[ Kim Whispering ]
A BIRD.

33:26.338 --> 33:29.041
WHAT KIND OF BIRD
WAS ON THE HOOD ORNAMENT?

33:29.075 --> 33:32.878
- A RAVEN.
- CORVUS CORAX.

33:32.911 --> 33:34.646
IS THAT GOOD?

33:34.680 --> 33:37.149
A RAVEN IS A MESSENGER
EITHER OF HOPE OR DOOM.

33:37.183 --> 33:39.051
WHICH IS IT HERE?

33:39.085 --> 33:41.120
YOU TELL ME.

33:47.526 --> 33:50.196
[ Hull Creaking ]
[ Water Dripping ]

33:50.229 --> 33:53.099
[ Sonar Pinging Slowly ]

34:05.711 --> 34:10.149
[ Pinging More Rapidly ]

34:19.891 --> 34:23.129
[ Pinging Slows Down ]

34:31.503 --> 34:34.106
[ Pinging Fades ]

34:41.079 --> 34:44.150
CHECKED OUT BY THEM
FROM THE SCHOOL LIBRARY.

34:44.183 --> 34:47.886
- I'M LISTENING.
- REINSTATE THE HUSBAND.

34:47.919 --> 34:50.156
WHY?

34:50.189 --> 34:52.791
IN A COMPRESSED ENVIRONMENT
LIKE THIS...

34:52.824 --> 34:56.228
WHERE THERE ARE SECRETS
STACKED ON TOP OF SECRETS,

34:56.262 --> 35:00.166
I THINK THIS IS
A SHARED CONSCIOUSNESS.

35:00.199 --> 35:03.735
SHE'S CHANNELING HER HUSBAND
IN THIS SOMEHOW.

35:03.769 --> 35:07.005
I DON'T KNOW WHAT THAT MEANS,
AND I GOT A MISSION
GOING DOWN THE DRAIN.

35:07.038 --> 35:11.109
SOMETHING'S WRONG
WITH THE MISSION PLAN.
I CAN'T TELL YOU WHAT IT IS.

35:11.143 --> 35:15.614
BUT SHE'S PICKING UP
A SENSE OF DOUBT ABOUT
THE MISSION FROM HER HUSBAND.

35:15.647 --> 35:19.418
DID YOU EVER HAVE
AN UNEXPLAINED PREMONITION?

35:19.451 --> 35:24.089
OF COURSE YOU HAVE.
YOU'VE TOLD THE STORY,
AND YOU'VE HEARD IT.

35:24.122 --> 35:28.327
"SOMETHING TOLD ME
TO GET DOWN.

35:28.360 --> 35:32.498
SOMETHING TOLD ME
NOT TO GET ON THAT PLANE."

35:32.531 --> 35:35.267
YOU'VE TOLD THAT STORY
AT THE "O" CLUB.

35:35.301 --> 35:39.838
EVERYONE HAS.
YOU KNOW IT'S TRUE.

35:39.871 --> 35:44.210
THE GIRL IS PICKING UP
A SENSE OF DOUBT
ABOUT THE MISSION.

35:46.245 --> 35:49.848
YOU GOT THE NAME RED CLOVER
FROM A BOOK
YOU READ YOUR DAUGHTER.

35:49.881 --> 35:54.186
YEAH. I KNEW
I'D SEEN IT SOMEWHERE.

35:54.220 --> 35:57.823
I HAD TO COME UP WITH
A CODE NAME FOR THE MISSION, AND
RED CLOVER JUST CAME TO ME.

35:57.856 --> 36:01.293
THE MISSION-- YOU HAVE DOUBTS.
WHAT'S WRONG WITH THIS MISSION?

36:01.327 --> 36:04.730
NOT A THING.
THE SPECS WERE GOOD.
I DON'T CARE ABOUT THE SPECS.

36:04.763 --> 36:07.399
THE SPECS CHECK OUT.
YOU'VE BEEN WORRIED
ABOUT SOMETHING.

36:07.433 --> 36:09.901
YOU HAVE BEEN.
YOU'RE DUTY, SOLDIER,

36:09.935 --> 36:12.804
IF YOU HAVE ANY DOUBTS,
IS TO EXPRESS THEM EARLY ON.

36:12.838 --> 36:16.174
NOT LATER, BUT NOW.
SOMETHING KEPT YOU
AWAKE AT NIGHT.

36:16.208 --> 36:18.910
- HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT, SIR?
- WHAT KEPT YOU UP, SOLDIER?

36:21.280 --> 36:24.182
- THE ORIGINAL SUB CAPTAIN.
- WHAT ABOUT HIM?

36:24.216 --> 36:26.352
HE CAME DOWN WITH THE FLU
JUST BEFORE THE MISSION.

36:26.385 --> 36:29.388
WE WEREN'T ABLE
TO FULLY VET THIS NEW GUY.

36:29.421 --> 36:31.757
THE SOUTH KOREANS PICKED HIM,
BUT I JUST DON'T KNOW
ENOUGH ABOUT HIM.

36:31.790 --> 36:33.292
AND?

36:35.461 --> 36:38.697
- IT MADE ME NERVOUS.
- IT MADE YOU NERVOUS,
BUT YOU DIDN'T SPEAK OUT.

36:38.730 --> 36:41.267
IT WAS JUST A FEELING.
YOU DON'T THROW AWAY A MISSION
BECAUSE YOU GET--

36:41.300 --> 36:43.269
WELL, LET'S ASSUME
THIS FEELING'S RIGHT.

36:43.302 --> 36:48.374
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN RIGHT NOW?
WHAT'S GOING ON
RIGHT NOW UNDERWATER?

36:53.078 --> 36:55.847
THIS IS A TIME ELAPSE SCAN
OF THAT SECTOR.

36:55.881 --> 36:58.216
WE'VE GOT A PLANE HERE.
WHAT'S THAT PLANE?

36:58.250 --> 37:01.019
- SUB-HUNTER.
- [ Bob ] ANY PINGS IN SECTOR?

37:01.052 --> 37:03.355
[ Man ]
DESTROYER HERE IN CRISSCROSS.

37:03.389 --> 37:05.957
WHAT WOULD YOU DO,
YOU WERE DOWN THERE?
MEANING WHAT WOULD JONAS DO?

37:05.991 --> 37:09.461
JUST TELL ME.
I'D HIDE, TRY TO CONVINCE THEM
IT WAS AN ANOMALY.

37:09.495 --> 37:13.799
A WHALE MOVING ALONG THE COAST.
THAT'S WHY WE CHOSE THAT SUB.
IT'S OLD, HAS NO FINGERPRINTS.

37:13.832 --> 37:16.468
BUT IF THE CAPTAIN ENDS UP BAD,
WHICH HE MUST'VE,
HE'S GONNA WANNA SIGNAL.

37:16.502 --> 37:18.370
JONAS HAS TO TAKE HIM OUT
AND GO WHERE?

37:18.404 --> 37:23.442
BOTTOM.
IS THAT BUCKET OF BOLTS
UP FOR IT?

37:23.475 --> 37:25.377
NOT MUCH CHOICE.
IT'S WHAT I'D DO.

37:25.411 --> 37:28.447
SURFACE WHERE AND WHEN?
UH--

37:28.480 --> 37:31.249
HERE.

37:31.283 --> 37:34.453
AS FAST AS I COULD,
ONCE THE NORTH KOREAN BOAT
LEFT ME ALONE.

37:40.125 --> 37:44.330
HOW LONG BEFORE
WE LOSE OUR HIGH TIDE?

37:44.363 --> 37:46.665
CAN YOU GET US
OFF THE BOTTOM, DRIFTING,
WITH MINIMAL SCREW NOISE?

37:48.500 --> 37:50.268
HOW ARE WE GONNA
GET OFF THE BOTTOM?

37:50.302 --> 37:52.471
CHIEF OF THE WATCH,
EMERGENCY BLOW TO MY MARK.

37:52.504 --> 37:57.008
- THROW THE CHICKEN SWITCHES.
- TO 40 FEET AND HOLD.

37:57.042 --> 37:59.845
- AHEAD FULL.
- [ Speaking Korean ]

38:30.241 --> 38:32.478
AT PERISCOPE DEPTH.

38:35.514 --> 38:38.617
SIX KILOMETERS
FROM INSERTION POINT.

38:38.650 --> 38:40.318
[ Grey ]
HIGH TIDE'S FOR ANOTHER HOUR.

38:45.357 --> 38:47.559
TAKE US TO 70 FEET
AND HOLD.

38:47.593 --> 38:51.196
AND ONCE WE'RE OUT, I WANT YOU
TO LAY DEAD ON THE BOTTOM
UNTIL YOU HEAR FROM US.

38:51.229 --> 38:54.332
SET YOUR BEACON
AT THIS FREQUENCY.

38:54.366 --> 38:56.768
LET'S HOPE THEY THOUGHT
TO LOOK FOR US HERE.

39:05.711 --> 39:08.480
[ Beeping ]

39:08.514 --> 39:11.049
WE ARE RECEIVING
A SIGNAL FROM SNAKE DOCTOR.

39:11.082 --> 39:13.151
THEY'RE AT
THE INSERTION POINT, SIR.

39:13.184 --> 39:16.755
GO AHEAD.
REWARD MY TRUST.

39:16.788 --> 39:20.291
SEND THE "GO" SIGNAL.

39:26.398 --> 39:30.469
THE TEAM HAS BEEN GIVEN
THE GREEN LIGHT TO GO ASHORE.

39:32.571 --> 39:35.306
LOWER HATCH IS SEALED.
FLOOD ON MY COMMAND.

39:39.711 --> 39:41.747
FLOOD VALVE IS OPEN.

39:41.780 --> 39:43.749
COMMENCE PRESSURIZATION
AT 70 FEET.

39:43.782 --> 39:46.685
HOW LONG?

39:46.718 --> 39:49.287
BY 0300,
PRESSURE SHOULD EQUALIZE.

39:49.320 --> 39:52.624
OR?
WE ALL START GETTING
REALLY BAD HEADACHES.

39:52.658 --> 39:54.760
LETS YOU KNOW YOUR BRAIN'S
ABOUT TO EXPLODE.

39:54.793 --> 39:56.595
SECURE FLOODING.

40:06.472 --> 40:09.307
WE GOT 30 SECONDS,
UNLESS YOU LIKE DROWNING.

40:11.577 --> 40:13.645
COME ON.

40:32.330 --> 40:36.635
WILL IT HOLD?
LONG ENOUGH.

40:36.668 --> 40:39.471
TIME LEFT?
FIVE MINUTES.

40:44.209 --> 40:47.212
OUR PRESSURIZATION'S SECURE.
UNDOG THE ESCAPE HATCH.

41:08.299 --> 41:10.502
[ Gasps ]
IT WON'T BUDGE.
[ Grey ] SPRING-LOADED.

41:10.536 --> 41:12.470
ONCE WE PRESSURIZE,
IT SHOULD POP.

41:12.504 --> 41:15.674
THE SPRING MUST BE CORRODED.

41:15.707 --> 41:19.845
MACK, LOOK AT ME.
YOUR FACE IS TWITCHING.
CONFIRMED.

41:19.878 --> 41:22.380
YOUR PULSE IS RACING.
I'M FINE.

41:22.413 --> 41:24.382
NARCOSIS?
MAYBE.

41:24.415 --> 41:26.652
WHAT'S YOUR WIFE'S NAME?

41:26.685 --> 41:28.954
LET ME UNDOG THE HATCH.
NO, NO.

41:28.987 --> 41:30.989
YOU STAY RIGHT OVER HERE.

41:53.679 --> 41:56.181
GOOD.

41:56.214 --> 42:00.686
ALL RIGHT.
I CAN TAP YOU OUT.

42:00.719 --> 42:02.854
FOUR TAPS,
THEY DRAIN THIS,

42:02.888 --> 42:05.724
WE CALL OFF THE MISSION,
RETHINK OUR OPTIONS.

42:05.757 --> 42:07.893
TIFFY. THAT'S MY WIFE.
I'M GOOD, TOP.

42:07.926 --> 42:10.862
ALL RIGHT THEN.

42:10.896 --> 42:13.832
STAY WITH ME.
DEEP BREATH.

42:13.865 --> 42:16.234
DON'T RISE FASTER
THAN MY BUBBLES.
THAT'S RIGHT.

42:49.735 --> 42:52.103
THE TEAM HAS THE PACKAGE
AT HIS COTTAGE.

42:52.137 --> 42:56.407
THEY'RE ON THEIR WAY BACK
TO THE SUB.
GOOD. GO HOME AND GET SOME REST.

42:56.441 --> 43:01.312
AS SOON AS THEY'RE BACK ON
THE SUB AND OUT OF NORTH KOREAN
WATERS, I'LL BE HAPPY TO.

43:01.346 --> 43:03.815
SHE SAW A MOVIE,
SHE READ A BOOK.

43:03.849 --> 43:07.485
NOTHING PARANORMAL.
JUST COINCIDENCE.
YOU MUST BE DISAPPOINTED.

43:07.518 --> 43:13.158
THERE ARE NUMEROUS POINTS
OF INTERSECTION BETWEEN THE REAL
MISSION AND KIM BROWN'S DREAM.

43:13.191 --> 43:16.061
YOU HAVE A THEORY?
OF COURSE I DO.

43:16.094 --> 43:19.765
ABOUT HER AND ABOUT
ALL YOUR UNIT WIVES.

43:19.798 --> 43:21.299
AMUSE ME.

43:21.332 --> 43:25.403
UNCONSCIOUS TRANSFERENCE.
DOESN'T EXIST.

43:25.436 --> 43:28.840
THESE WOMEN LAY THEIR HEADS
ON PILLOWS EVERY NIGHT...

43:28.874 --> 43:31.643
NEXT TO MEN YOU TRAINED
TO KEEP SECRETS.

43:31.677 --> 43:34.813
HAVE YOU EVER CHEATED
ON YOUR WIFE?

43:34.846 --> 43:38.650
NO.
WHY?

43:38.684 --> 43:40.518
BECAUSE IF I DID,
SHE'D KNOW IT.

43:40.551 --> 43:44.389
THAT'S CORRECT.
THANK YOU, COLONEL.

43:45.724 --> 43:47.826
CAN WE USE THOUGHT CONTROL
AS A WEAPON?

43:47.859 --> 43:50.461
NOT YET.

44:12.718 --> 44:14.820
[ Cawing ]

44:26.898 --> 44:29.701
[ Call And Response ]
* FIRED UP
FIRED UP *

44:37.175 --> 44:39.577
* TWENTY-SEVEN
FIRED UP **
